  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Anticipatory Response for South West Monsoon Flooding</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Anticipated risk (cyclical displacement being exacerbated by the COVID-19 situation): Three of the COVID19 high-risk districts are among the most vulnerable regions to receive high concentration of rainfall during the South-west monsoon season between May to September. 45% of the flood as well as landslide affected persons since 2014 are from these 03 districts. Present lockdown and travel restrictions have severely impacted coordination between the actors and preparation efforts on all levels. Shortage of facilities in safe centres (designated and not designated/communal ones) impacts on a family&apos;s decision to evacuate because of the fear of being infected with COVID19 and they might decide to stay at homes taking the risk of their own lives.</narrative>
  </description>
